# TradeGuard API (Python)

## Layout

- `apps/api/app/main.py` — FastAPI app, CORS, lifespan
- `apps/api/app/core/` — config, auth, middleware, user context
- `apps/api/app/api/routes/` — HTTP routes
- `apps/api/app/services/` — business logic
- `apps/api/app/risk/` — risk engine (veto power)
- `apps/api/app/agents/` — orchestrator + LLM

## User scoping

- `UserContextMiddleware` sets per-request user id via `resolve_request_user_id`.
- Use `get_current_user_id()` / `user_scope()` from `app/core/user_context.py`.
- Global OAuth state uses `GLOBAL_USER_ID = "_global"` in `robinhood_connect.py`.

## Storage

- Call `get_storage()` only after `init_storage()` in app lifespan.
- `app_state.key` is VARCHAR(64) — keep composite keys under 64 chars.
- Postgres backend: `STORAGE_BACKEND=postgres` in production.

## Config

- New env vars go in `apps/api/app/core/config.py` and `apps/api/.env.example`.
- Document production vars in `docs/RAILWAY.md`.

## Provider pattern

Market, embeddings, alerts, and MCP use mock-first `auto` mode. Follow existing provider abstractions — do not require live API keys in dev or tests.
